      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Dr. Jerry France (Kent's First Wife)\n\n### Background Summary\n\n**Early Life:**\n- Raised in \"strict Mormon household\" (her words)\n- Knocked up at age 14\n- Married by age 14\n- Bookie turned psychologist\n\n**Where They Married:**\n- **Baháʼí Temple in Chicago**\n- (New info this episode)\n\n### Career\n\n**Creator of Tesseract Model:**\n- Designed psychological methods for elite school\n- Erica attended this school\n\n**Radford University:**\n- Given entire research center\n- **Gender research center**\n- **University seal/yearbook: The Beehive**\n- \"I can't make it up. I cannot make it up.\"\n\n**Corporate Work:**\n- DuPont Chemicals psychologist\n- Bush family connections\n- Organizational psychology\n\n**Eastern Europe Research:**\n- Conducted gender research in Eastern Europe\n- Specifically Bosnia\n- \"So many ties to Eastern Europe\"\n- \"We're going to get into that\"\n\n### The Pattern\n\n**All roads lead to:**\n- Military/intelligence operations\n- Elite families\n- Gender/psychology programs\n- Eastern Europe connections"
      }
    },
