      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## The Name Problem\n\n### Erica's Maternal Grandmother\n\n**From 1970 Obituary:**\n\nAngelina **Lombardo** Abbis\n- Wife of Joseph Abbis\n- Cincinnati, Ohio\n- Died 1970\n\n### The Photos\n\n**Candace's Observation:**\n\"Once I heard him say it, Lori and her sister Deborah **do look like Vince**.\n\nI see it.\"\n\n**The Mystery:**\n\"I thought it was interesting that I could never find a photo of her parents.\"\n\n### Lombardo = Lombardi?\n\n**Charlie's Confirmation:**\n\"He says she's a **Lombardi**.\n\nBut actually, according to obituary, she's a **Lombardo**.\n\nIf that's the reality, if those are interchangeable, then we can begin to honestly speculate about Lorie's potential ties to the **Lombardo Genovese crime family**, who had a lot to do with illegal gambling and racketeering.\n\n**It's now all open. It's all on the table and it is all of interest.**\"\n\n### The Unanswered Questions\n\n**Candace's Appeal:**\n\"Is her name really Angelina Lombardo? Is his name Joe Lombardo?\n\nI don't know.\n\nIs Lori actually Vince's kid? Did he have one out of wedlock?\n\nI don't know.\n\nBut a **direct descendant** means a direct descendant.\n\n**That's to me is the only possibility.**\n\nWhy else would you be getting the paraphernalia which is **worth a fortune**?\"\n\n### The Gambling Connection\n\n**If Lombardo/Lombardi are interchangeable:**\n- Opens door to **Lombardo Genovese crime family**\n- Illegal gambling operations\n- Racketeering\n- Fits pattern: \"From her parents to her grandparents... lotteries, casinos, gambling. These are familial themes.\"\n\n### Left for Sleuths\n\n\"Unfortunately, there are no photos of Lori's father and mother that I could find.\n\nBut it's a strong lead, and I'm going to leave it at that for YouTubers and other sleuths to take a look at.\""
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "dddddddd-dddd-4ddd-8ddd-dddddddddddd",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Khazarian Mafia History Lesson",
      "position": {
        "x": 600,
        "y": 1760
      },
      "width": 500,
      "height": 800,
      "color": "#bf360c",
      "ports": [
        {
